The paper deals with the problem of perfect secret key generation in a network model, which involves communication over a public channel and an eavesdropper. This problem is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The algorithmic approach based on Steiner tree packing suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of a public channel and the network model suggest that the paper may also be relevant to computer communication (cs.CC) and networking (cs.NI).
